content.description: This is the fourth bolted route encounteded on the east wall as you hike up the slot canyon leading to the little narrows.  I have not climbed the route so the rating is just what I thought it looked like.  If anyone has any more info please post it in the comments so that I can update the route.
content.protection: 5 bolts to 2 bolt anchor with quicklinks

content.description: This is the second route encountered as you head up to the little narrows.  The crux is getting to the third bolt.
This is the third bolted route encountered as you head up the slot canyon leading to the little narrows.  This is the most overhung route of the three just before the canyon narrows down.
content.protection: 6 bolts to 2 bolt anchor (anchor has no chains, rings, or quicklinks, it is just two standard hangers)

content.description: This route climbs past 2 drilled angles and 1 bolt which can't be seen from the ground to chain anchors at the top.  The crux is just past the first pin.  If anyone knows any info on the name or FA of this route let me know so I can add it to the description.
content.protection: 2 drilled pins and one bolt to a chain anchor.
content.location: There are currently four sport routes on the east side of the slot canyon leading up to the "Little Narrows", this is the first route encountered.  Two drilled angles can be seen from the ground.
